Bobby Hutchins https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bobby_Hutchins 0 Robert E. "Bobby" Hutchins (March 29, 1925 – May 17, 1945) was an American child actor who was a regular in the Our Gang short subjects series from 1927 to 1933. A native of Tacoma, Washington, he was given the nickname of Wheezer after running around the studios on his first day so much that he began to wheeze.
